---
import WikiLayout from '../../layouts/WikiLayout.astro';
import { linkKeywords } from '../../utils/linkKeywords';
---
<WikiLayout title="Weapons" section="weapons" description="Every weapon in Davy Jones' Deckhand — Mop, Saber, Rapier, Claw, and more. Each weapon defines your starting deck and stances. Pick the right one to power your roguelike deckbuilder run.">
  <div class="wiki-content">
    <h1>Weapons</h1>
    <p>
      Your choice of weapon defines your starting deck and unlocks a unique set of stances for the voyage.
      Weapons are selected at port before setting sail and cannot be changed mid-voyage.
    </p>
    <div class="stub-notice">Full weapon data will be added as the game develops.</div>

    <h2>Known Weapons</h2>
    <table class="weapons-table">
      <thead>
        <tr><th>Weapon</th><th>Notes</th><th class="demo-col">Available in Demo</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td class="weapon-name">Mop</td><td class="weapon-notes" set:html={linkKeywords("Tom's first weapon. The tutorial is fought with a mop. A fully viable playstyle.")} /><td class="demo-cell demo-yes">✓</td></tr>
        <tr><td class="weapon-name">Saber</td><td class="weapon-notes" set:html={linkKeywords("A balanced weapon that comes with the Ring of Return starter artefact.")} /><td class="demo-cell demo-yes">✓</td></tr>
        <tr><td class="weapon-name">Broken Mop</td><td class="weapon-notes" set:html={linkKeywords("Available after Tom's (first) death. This weapon features low stamina, high health, the Tentacle starter artefact, and a starter deck full of sacrificial cards.")} /><td class="demo-cell demo-yes">✓</td></tr>
        <tr><td class="weapon-name">The Claw</td><td class="weapon-notes" set:html={linkKeywords("A battle-axe crafted from a stick and the claw of a giant crab. This weapon features low base stamina but powerful stances with extremely high damage, and a unique RAGE card that gives a large stamina boost once per combat.")} /><td class="demo-cell demo-no">✗</td></tr>
        <tr><td class="weapon-name">Rapier</td><td class="weapon-notes" set:html={linkKeywords("Weak damage but very strong counter-attack damage. Comes with a leeway focused starter deck and the Sharpening Stone.", undefined, ['WEAK', 'ATTACK DAMAGE'])} /><td class="demo-cell demo-no">✗</td></tr>
        <tr><td class="weapon-name">Dual Buckets</td><td class="weapon-notes" set:html={linkKeywords("A bucket on each fist. The Broken Mirror. This weapon starts with low damage but scales surprisingly well.")} /><td class="demo-cell demo-no">✗</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <p>See also: <a href="/stances">Stances</a> for weapon-specific stance cards.</p>
  </div>
</WikiLayout>

<style>
  .demo-col {
    text-align: center;
    white-space: nowrap;
  }

  .demo-cell {
    text-align: center;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  .demo-yes { color: #3a9e5f; }
  .demo-no  { color: #b94040; }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .weapons-table thead {
      display: none;
    }

    .weapons-table tbody tr {
      display: block;
      padding: 0.75rem 0;
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    }

    .weapons-table tbody tr:last-child {
      border-bottom: none;
    }

    .weapons-table td {
      display: inline;
      border: none;
      padding: 0;
      background: none;
    }

    .weapon-name {
      display: inline !important;
      font-weight: 700;
      color: var(--navy);
      font-size: 1rem;
    }

    .demo-cell {
      display: inline-flex !important;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 0.3rem;
      margin-left: 0.4rem;
      font-size: 0.85rem;
      font-weight: 600;
    }

    .demo-yes::after { content: ' Available in demo'; }
    .demo-no::after  { content: ' Not in demo'; }

    .weapon-notes {
      display: block !important;
      margin-top: 0.3rem;
      font-size: 0.88rem;
      color: var(--text-muted);
    }
  }
</style>
